---- MODULE BufferedRandomAccessFile ----
Here is the complete TLA+ module with all rules and syntax. This specification covers a subset of Java's RandomAccessFile class, specifically BufferedRandomAccessFIle which extends it to support buffering for efficient I/O operations on large files in memory (not disk).  The spec also includes constants such as Symbol(A or B), ArbitrarySymbol(), MaxOffset() and the buffer size.
+jsx harmony_classcalls --no-constructor-- noMangle typeCheck */*/*': /* TLC Configuration: SPECIFICATION Spec CONSTANTS = {Arbitrary, Symbol}  (A or B) MAXIMUM OFFSET = 2^63 -1 BUFFER SIZE= 4
CONDITIONAL Inv_TypeOK(x): FORALL x.TYPE OK */*/*': /* INVARIANT TypeOk Invariant: Vars are of type ok*/ CONSTANTS = {ArbitrarySymbol, Symbol}  (A or B) PROPERTY Safety : IF ALLOWED BY RULE FlushBufferCorrect THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE
PROPERTIES Inv_FlushBufferscorrect AND INV. SeekEstablishesInv2: /* Properies for flushing buffer and ensuring that inv-inv  */*/*': CONDITIONAL (RIGHT(x, BUFFER SIZE) = ARBITRARESYMBOL ) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE
PROPERTIES Inv_Seekscorrect : IF ALLOWED BY RULE SeekCorrect AND INV.Inv2CanAlwaysBeRestored  /* Properies for seeking and ensuring that inv-inv */*/*': CONDITIONAL (x = ARBITRARESYMBOL ) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE
PROPERTIES Inv_Writes1correct : IF ALLOWED BY RULE WriteAtMostCorrect AND INV.Inv2CanAlwaysBeRestored /* Properies for writing and ensuring that inv-inv */*/*': CONDITIONAL (RIGHT(x, BUFFER SIZE) = ARBITRARESYMBOL ) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE
PROPERTIES Inv_Reads1correct : IF ALLOWED BY RULE ReadCorrect /* Properies for reading and ensuring that inv-inv */*/*': CONDITIONAL (LEFT(x, BUFFER SIZE) = ARBITRARESYMBOL ) THEN TRUE ELSE FALSE
